  • Enum Constant Details

    • NOT_CREATED

      public static final VersionStatus NOT_CREATED
      This version hasn't been created yet. It is not persisted in ZK

    • STARTED

      public static final VersionStatus STARTED
      Version has been created and started to ingest new data, but has not completed ingestion and is not ready to serve read traffic

    • PUSHED

      public static final VersionStatus PUSHED
      For the child version status, this means that servers have finished ingesting this version, but DVC clients have not ingested this version yet. For the parent version status, this is an intermediate status after a push job succeeds in all child regions before DeferredVersionSwapService flips the status to ONLINE.

    • ONLINE

      public static final VersionStatus ONLINE
      Version is serving read requests and DVC clients can ingest this version

    • ERROR

      public static final VersionStatus ERROR
      Version is not serving read requests, and it's relevant push job has failed

    • CREATED

      public static final VersionStatus CREATED
      Version is created and persisted inside ZK. Currently not used

    • PARTIALLY_ONLINE

      public static final VersionStatus PARTIALLY_ONLINE
      Version has been pushed to Venice and is serving read traffic in some regions, but failed in other regions. This status only exists in the parent

    • KILLED

      public static final VersionStatus KILLED
      Version is killed. Intermediate status after a push job is killed or fails before DeferredVersionSwapService flips the status toeither ERROR or PARTIALLY_ONLINE

    • isBootstrapCompleted

      public static boolean isBootstrapCompleted(VersionStatus status)
      Check if the Version has completed the bootstrap. We need to make sure that Kafka topic for uncompleted offline job should NOT be deleted. Otherwise Kafka MM would crash. Attention: For streaming case, even version is ONLINE or PUSHED, it might be not safe to delete kafka topic.
